body:
@vkjr, realizing I meant to ask that although font-family is implemented correctly, we'd still need to include "SFProText" in a place where it could be referenced though, right? It looks like through http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qfontdatabase.html 

Currently there are a couple of possible font directories, one in both `status-react` and `react-native-desktop`, but I'm not totally sure how this would be incorporated into the above library. 

<blockquote><img src="//d33sqmjvzgs8hq.cloudfront.net/wp-content/themes/oneqt/assets/images/favicon.ico.gzip" width="48" align="right"><div><strong><a href="http://doc.qt.io/qt-5/qfontdatabase.html">QFontDatabase Class | Qt GUI 5.11</a></strong></div></blockquote>

@vkjr @rcullito  I would go with Arial for Linux, and SF for OSX.

Here is an example of how the chat screen looks with Arial >> **zpl.io/amnlnEv** (Zeplin)

For Linux, we should replace all the SF font-weight: semibold & font-weight: bold  to **bold** in Arial.
